I really despise stuff that leads nowhere. It's not a Darwinian genetics thing, just curiosity at what life has to offer. You can bring something new not out of death, but out of non-existence itself. Anything possible but outside of existence begs to be let in. Leibniz said it.

It's because people treat heredity as "building blocks" or a Minecraft "starting seed", instead of seeing it extend indefinitely. You get to see the other person combined with yourself, see them in a new context, give them a new life, multiply them. You extend them through time.

I don't like it when people just make up fake stuff for the bottom layer of iceberg tier memes. There are more than enough obscure ideas, concepts, and theories in any field to fill at least ten icebergs of depth down without resorting to forgery. Maybe makes me a fake Borgesian.

This account basically started with me making a thread explaining every single entity on the original /x/ iceberg meme, including the ones everyone thought were just jokes. Any iceberg meme I've made had real stuff - top to bottom. It's called craftsmanship. Durer talks about it.
